net.peierls.expr

Class Expression

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.peierls.expr.Expression
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConstantExpression, ExtendedExpression, LetExpression, OperationExpression, VariableExpression

    public abstract class Expression
extends Object
    A double-precision arithmetic expression on constants, variables, unary and binary operations, with local binding of variables to subexpressions, supporting evaluation and formatting (string representation).

        protected <R> R accept(Visitor<R> visitor)
        Apply a visitor function to this expression. The default implementation is to call the Visitor.visitUnknown(net.peierls.expr.Expression) method, but subclasses should override to call the visit method on one of the concrete subclasses known to the visitor interface.

        public final double evaluate()

        Throws:
        DivisionByZeroException - if a division reults in positive or negative infinity or NaN
        UnboundVariableException - if the expression has a free variable
